Single-subproblem example
=========================

Problem
-------
Minimize  -x1 - 2*x2
Subject to
  x1 <= 3         (subproblem constraint)
  x2 <= 4         (subproblem constraint)
  2*x1 + 3*x2 = 10  (coupling constraint, master)
  x1, x2 >= 0

Known optimal
-------------
x1 = 0, x2 = 10/3 ≈ 3.333333
Objective = -2 * (10/3) = -6.667 (relaxed)

Code path exercised
-------------------
num_clients = 1: the semaphore-based service queue in phase_2_iteration()
processes exactly one subproblem per master iteration.  This exercises the
single-client branch of the service-queue loop and the associated critical
section around sub_data[0].
